# skedyul-node: PR prerelease + Publish to NPM

This package is published to npm as **`skedyul`**. Default branch is **`master`**.

## Workflow layout

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| **`publish.yml`** | Reusable **`workflow_call` only** — runs `npm publish` (npm trusted publisher target) |
| **`release-stable.yml`** | Manual **`workflow_dispatch`** — Copilot bump, commit, calls `publish.yml`, git tag |
| **`pr-automate.yml`** | PR open/sync — template, docs, prerelease version, calls `publish.yml` |

npm OIDC only trusts **one workflow filename**. Register **`publish.yml`** on npmjs.com.

## PR automation (`pr-automate.yml`)

On every PR open/sync against `master`:

1. Plan-style PR template + classification labels
2. Copilot syncs `README.md` and `docs/*.md`
3. Prerelease semver: `{nextMinor}.0-alpha.{prNumber}.{sync}`
4. Calls **`publish.yml`** with dist-tag **`alpha`**
5. Commits docs + version, git tag `v{prerelease}`

Skip with `<!-- skip-pr-template -->` in the PR body.

## Stable release (manual)

```bash
gh workflow run "Publish to NPM" --repo skedyul/skedyul-node --ref master
```

(`release-stable.yml` — Copilot picks patch/minor, commits version, calls **`publish.yml`** with dist-tag **`latest`**, tags `vX.Y.Z`.)

## npm trusted publisher

On [npmjs.com](https://www.npmjs.com/package/skedyul/access) → Trusted Publisher:

- Repository: `skedyul/skedyul-node`
- Workflow filename: **`publish.yml`**

Parent workflows (`pr-automate.yml`, `release-stable.yml`) must call `publish.yml`; do not run `npm publish` elsewhere.

## Related (monorepo)

Integration apps pin exact `skedyul` versions. See `.cursor/rules/skedyul-dependency-versions.mdc` in the app repo.
